</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,788]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,691,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Dworakowska, 1977" authorityName="Dworakowska" authorityYear="1977" box="[663,1093,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gucia">
<emphasis box="[663,850,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Empoasca gucia</emphasis>
Dworakowska, 
<number box="[1034,1093,692,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1977.0">1977</number>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the sinuate central part of the pygofer processes, and in having the aedeagus shaft compressed and with a long appendage from the apical ventral margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
